{"title_page": "Emmanuel Akwasi Gyamfi", "text_new": "{{Infobox officeholder\n| honorific-prefix =\n| name = Emmanuel Akwasi Gyamfi\n| honorific-suffix =\n| image = \n| alt = \n| constituency_MP = [[Odotobri Constituency]]\n| parliament = Ghana\n| majority =\n| predecessor =\n| successor = \n| term_start =\n| term_end =\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1974|12|1}}\n| birth_place =\n| death_date =\n| death_place =\n| nationality = Ghanaian\n| spouse =\n| party = [[New Patriotic Party]]\n| relations =\n| children =\n| residence =\n| alma_mater =\n| occupation =\n| profession =\n| signature =\n| signature_alt =\n| website =\n| footnotes =\n}}\n\n'''Emmanuel Akwasi Gyamfi''' is a Ghanaian politician and member of the [[MPs elected in the Ghanaian parliamentary election, 2016|Seventh Parliament of the Fourth Republic of Ghana]] representing the Odotobri Constituency in the [[Ashanti Region]] on the ticket of the New Patriotic Party.<ref>https://www.parliament.gh/mps?mp=196</ref>\n\n== Personal life and Education ==\nEmmanuel was born on 1 December, 1974 in a town known as Homase No. 2 in his region. He had his Bachelor of Science degree in Planning from Kwame Nkruma University of Science and Technology, Kumasi. Prior to his appointment into parliament, He worked as a project manager at Odotobri Rural Bank Limited. He is a Christian and married with five children.<br />\n\n== Political Career ==\nHe was elected into parliament on 7 January, 2013 after the completion of the 2012 Ghanaian General Elections. He was then reelected on 7 January, 2017 after the 2016 Ghanaian General Elections where he obtained  66.13% of the valid votes cast. \n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Gyamfi, Emmanuel Akwasi}}\n[[Category:Ghanaian MPs 2017\u2013]]\n[[Category:1974 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:New Patriotic Party politicians]]\n\n\n{{Ghana-politician-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox officeholder\n| honorific-prefix =\n| name = Emmanuel Akwasi Gyamfi\n| honorific-suffix =\n| image = \n| alt = \n| constituency_MP = [[Odotobri Constituency]]\n| parliament = Ghana\n| majority =\n| predecessor =\n| successor = \n| term_start =\n| term_end =\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1974|12|1}}\n| birth_place =\n| death_date =\n| death_place =\n| nationality = Ghanaian\n| spouse =\n| party = [[New Patriotic Party]]\n| relations =\n| children =\n| residence =\n| alma_mater =\n| occupation =\n| profession =\n| signature =\n| signature_alt =\n| website =\n| footnotes =\n}}\n\n'''Emmanuel Akwasi Gyamfi''' is a Ghanaian politician and member of the [[MPs elected in the Ghanaian parliamentary election, 2016|Seventh Parliament of the Fourth Republic of Ghana]] representing the Odotobri Constituency in the [[Ashanti Region]] on the ticket of the New Patriotic Party.<ref>https://www.parliament.gh/mps?mp=196</ref>\n\n== Personal life and Education ==\nEmmanuel was born on 1 December , 1974 in a town known as Homase No. 2 in his region. He had his Bachelor of Science degree in Planning from Kwame Nkruma University of Science and Technology, Kumasi. Prior to his appointment into parliament, He worked as a project manager at Odotobri Rural Bank Limited. He is a christian and married with five children.<br />\n\n== Political Career ==\nHe was elected into parliament on 7 January, 2013 after the completion of the 2012 Ghanaian General Elections. He was then reelected on 7 January, 2017 after the 2016 Ghanaian General Elections where he obtained  66.13% of the valid votes cast. \n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Gyamfi, Emmanuel Akwasi}}\n[[Category:Ghanaian MPs 2017\u2013]]\n[[Category:1974 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:New Patriotic Party politicians]]\n\n\n{{Ghana-politician-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Iridescent", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200ePersonal life and Education:Cleanup andtypo fixing,typo(s) fixed: christian \u2192 Christian,  ,  \u2192 ,", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emmanuel_Akwasi_Gyamfi"}
{"title_page": "George Mireku Duker", "text_new": "{{Infobox officeholder\n| honorific-prefix =\n| name = George Mireku Duker\n| honorific-suffix =\n| image = \n| alt = \n| constituency_MP = [[Tarkwa-Nsuaem Constituency]]\n| parliament = Ghana\n| majority =\n| predecessor =\n| successor = \n| term_start =\n| term_end =\n| birth_date =\n| birth_place =\n| death_date =\n| death_place =\n| nationality = Ghanaian\n| spouse =\n| party = [[New Patriotic Party]]\n| relations =\n| children =\n| residence =\n| alma_mater =\n| occupation =\n| profession =\n| signature =\n| signature_alt =\n| website =\n| footnotes =\n}}\n\n'''George Mireku Duker''' (born Friday, 9th May, 1975)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.parliament.gh/mps?mp=242|title=Parliament of Ghana|website=www.parliament.gh|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref> is a Ghanaian politician and member of the [[MPs elected in the Ghanaian parliamentary election, 2016|Seventh Parliament of the Fourth Republic of Ghana]] representing the [[Tarkwa-Nsuaem (Ghana parliament constituency)|Tarkwa-Nsuaem]] Constituency in the [[Western Region (Ghana)|Western Region]] on the ticket of the New Patriotic Party.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ghanamps.com/mps/|title=Ghana MPs - List of MPs|website=www.ghanamps.com|access-date=2019-02-15}}</ref>\n\n== Politics ==\nHe was first elected to parliament in 2016 and is a member of the [[New Patriotic Party]]. He pulled more votes for the [[New Patriotic Party]], in the [[Western Region (Ghana)|Western Region of Ghana]].\n\n== Early life and Education ==\nHe was born on 9th May, 1975. Duker studied B.ED ACCOUNTING [[University of Education, Winneba|UNIVERSITY OF EDUCATION]] - KUMASI CAMPUS, later MSC OIL AND GAS MANAGEMENT [[University of Plymouth|UNIVERSITY OF PLYMOUTH - UK]]\n\n== Career ==\nPrior to parliament, he served as a teacher from 1998-2006 ([[Ghana Education Service|GHANA EDUCATION SERVICE]]), Special Aide from 2007-2008 (MINISTRY OF LOCAL GOVERNMENT, Ghana), Municipal Chief Executive under President [[John Kufuor|John Agyekum Kuffour]] administration in 2008. Duker was also the Programs Manager of  Integrated Social Development Centre (ISODEC)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.parliament.gh/mps?mp=242|title=Parliament of Ghana|website=www.parliament.gh|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.isodec.org/|title=isodec.org|website=www.isodec.org|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref> from 2011 - 2012\n\n== Committee assignments ==\n\n* Mines and Energy, Vice Chairman\n* Holding Offices of Profit, Member\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Duker, George Mireku}}\n[[Category:Ghanaian MPs 2017\u2013]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:New Patriotic Party politicians]]\n\n\n{{Ghana-politician-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox officeholder\n| honorific-prefix =\n| name = George Mireku Duker\n| honorific-suffix =\n| image = \n| alt = \n| constituency_MP = [[Tarkwa-Nsuaem Constituency]]\n| parliament = Ghana\n| majority =\n| predecessor =\n| successor = \n| term_start =\n| term_end =\n| birth_date =\n| birth_place =\n| death_date =\n| death_place =\n| nationality = Ghanaian\n| spouse =\n| party = [[New Patriotic Party]]\n| relations =\n| children =\n| residence =\n| alma_mater =\n| occupation =\n| profession =\n| signature =\n| signature_alt =\n| website =\n| footnotes =\n}}\n\n'''George Mireku Duker''' (born Friday, 9th May, 1975)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.parliament.gh/mps?mp=242|title=Parliament of Ghana|website=www.parliament.gh|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref> is a Ghanaian politician and member of the [[MPs elected in the Ghanaian parliamentary election, 2016|Seventh Parliament of the Fourth Republic of Ghana]] representing the [[Tarkwa-Nsuaem (Ghana parliament constituency)|Tarkwa-Nsuaem]] Constituency in the [[Western Region (Ghana)|Western Region]] on the ticket of the New Patriotic Party.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ghanamps.com/mps/|title=Ghana MPs - List of MPs|website=www.ghanamps.com|access-date=2019-02-15}}</ref>\n\n== Politics ==\nHe was first elected to parliament in 2016 and is a member of the [[New Patriotic Party]]. He pulled more votes for the [[New Patriotic Party]], in the [[Western Region (Ghana)|Western Region of Ghana]].\n\n== Early life and Education ==\nHe was born on 9th May, 1975. Duker studied B.ED ACCOUNTING [[University of Education, Winneba|UNIVERSITY OF EDUCATION]] - KUMASI CAMPUS, later MSC OIL AND GAS MANAGEMENT [[University of Plymouth|UNIVERSITY OF PLYMOUTH - UK]]\n\n== Career ==\nPrior to parliament, he served as a teacher from 1998-2006 ([[Ghana Education Service|GHANA EDUCATION SERVICE]]), Special Aide from 2007-2008 (MINISTRY OF LOCAL GOVERNMENT, Ghana), Municipal Chief Executive under President [[John Kufuor|John Agyekum Kuffour]] adminstration in 2008. Duker was also the Programs Manager of  Integrated Social Development Centre (ISODEC)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.parliament.gh/mps?mp=242|title=Parliament of Ghana|website=www.parliament.gh|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.isodec.org/|title=isodec.org|website=www.isodec.org|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref> from 2011 - 2012\n\n== Committee assignments ==\n\n* Mines and Energy, Vice Chairman\n* Holding Offices of Profit, Member\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Duker, George Mireku}}\n[[Category:Ghanaian MPs 2017\u2013]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:New Patriotic Party politicians]]\n\n\n{{Ghana-politician-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Iridescent", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eCareer:Cleanup andtypo fixing,typo(s) fixed: adminstration \u2192 administration", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/George_Mireku_Duker"}
